./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:2734:./docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S3-lock-design.codex.log:1574:   103	`python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --teardown` runs the same auth, identity, sandbox, and pre-clean path, then stops after deleting SDK-managed records in the sandbox shared folder. The delete guard lives in `sandbox.teardown_records()`: it lists records in the target shared folder, reads each record's `keeper_declarative_manager` marker, decodes it, and deletes only records whose decoded payload has `manager == MANAGER_NAME`.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:2735:./docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S3-lock-design.codex.log:2122:   368	- 2026-04-26 [codex-cli][bg-detach] **Background launchers must use `nohup` + runner-script + redirect-from-/dev/null, not `( ... ) &`.** Cursor's Shell tool starts a fresh bash per command that exits when the command returns. Naive `( ... ) &` subshells inherit that bash as their parent and catch SIGHUP when it exits — the cleanup block (writing `STATE=DONE` to the marker) never runs. First version of `codex_offline_bg.sh` had this bug; bus.py worker completed a clean READONLY-OK memo in the log but the marker stayed `LAUNCHED` forever. Fix: write the codex command + cleanup into a runner script (`/tmp/codex-offline-<ts>-<pid>.runner.sh`) and launch via `nohup bash $RUNNER </dev/null >/dev/null 2>&1 &`. `disown` alone is not enough on macOS bash inside an exiting parent. Verified: trivial test prompt now writes `STATE=DONE EXIT_CODE=0` correctly within seconds of codex finishing.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:2736:./docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S3-lock-design.codex.log:2285:/Users/martin/Downloads/LESSONS.md:418:- 2026-04-27 [smoke][marker-manager-is-core-contract] **SDK ownership `manager` (`keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:27` `MANAGER_NAME = "keeper-pam-declarative"`) is a core ownership invariant, NOT a smoke-local knob.** Sprint 7h-36 CDX-1 explored multi-profile refactor; intuitive answer "give each profile its own manager string" was rejected because `compute_diff` treats non-`MANAGER_NAME` markers as conflicts at `keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:441-451` and orphan deletion narrows by `manager == MANAGER_NAME` at `keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:527-535`. Multi-profile parallelism MUST isolate by folder/project/title only. Pattern: when a refactor proposal touches a constant that participates in core type/diff invariants, cite the diff/conflict semantics before changing it; "make it a parameter" is a wrong instinct here. The right knob is the *scope* (folder, project name, record-title prefix), not the *identity* (manager string).
